.TH "BSON_APPEND_CODE" "3" "2014-08-19" "libbson"
.SH NAME
bson_append_code()
.SH "SYNOPSIS"

.nf
.nf
bool
bson_append_code (bson_t     *bson,
                  const char *key,
                  int         key_length,
                  const char *javascript);
.fi
.fi

.SH "PARAMETERS"

.TP
.B bson
A
.BR bson_t
\&.
.LP
.TP
.B key
The key name.
.LP
.TP
.B key_length
The length of
.B key
or -1 to use strlen().
.LP
.TP
.B javascript
A UTF-8 encoded string containing the javascript.
.LP

.SH "DESCRIPTION"

The
.BR bson_append_code(3)
function shall append a new element to
.B bson
using the UTF-8 encoded
.B javascript
provided.
.B javascript
must be a NULL terminated C string.

.SH "RETURNS"

true if the operation was applied successfully, otherwise false and
.B bson
should be discarded.


